how do I deal with it,

00:40:00.900 --> 00:40:03.390
I feel a particular
responsibility

00:40:03.390 --> 00:40:04.930
to deal with that.

00:40:04.930 --> 00:40:07.140
And I feel a particular
responsibility in the fact

00:40:07.140 --> 00:40:13.800
that this is my job
to be willing to bear

00:40:13.800 --> 00:40:16.709
a bit more of that burden
of humanizing and educating.

00:40:16.709 --> 00:40:18.250
I think there are
a couple of things.

00:40:18.250 --> 00:40:20.130
One, there are
certain things that I

00:40:20.130 --> 00:40:23.190
am firm about that I'm
not going to talk about.

00:40:23.190 --> 00:40:25.470
My personal medical
history is just that.

00:40:25.470 --> 00:40:26.880
It's personal.

00:40:26.880 --> 00:40:31.770
And I am pretty
clear, particularly

00:40:31.770 --> 00:40:35.420
if a reporter asks me about
that, that I politely push back

00:40:35.420 --> 00:40:36.420
and just say, I'm sorry.

00:40:36.420 --> 00:40:37.780
I'm not comfortable
talking about that,

00:40:37.780 --> 00:40:38.970
certainly not on the record.

00:40:42.097 --> 00:40:43.680
There are some people
who aren't going

00:40:43.680 --> 00:40:46.860
to change their mind either
ever or in one sitting,

00:40:46.860 --> 00:40:50.700
and I think understanding that
and sort of freeing myself

00:40:50.700 --> 00:40:53.340
from that responsibility of
feeling like if I don't change

00:40:53.340 --> 00:40:57.540
everyone from A to Z in one
sitting then I've failed,

00:40:57.540 --> 00:41:01.950
or I'm not doing a good job,
I think that's been freeing

00:41:01.950 --> 00:41:02.850
in many ways.

00:41:02.850 --> 00:41:03.780
My approach is this.

00:41:07.110 --> 00:41:10.900
I know that there's a lot
of ignorance out there.

00:41:10.900 --> 00:41:13.200
I want allies to
educate themselves,

00:41:13.200 --> 00:41:15.900
but I understand that it's
also difficult to not know

00:41:15.900 --> 00:41:17.200
what you don't know.

00:41:17.200 --> 00:41:19.120
And so people are
going to make mistakes.

00:41:19.120 --> 00:41:23.490
People are going to come in
with knowledge gaps that exist.

00:41:23.490 --> 00:41:27.920
If you're coming to me
with a genuine interest,

00:41:27.920 --> 00:41:31.530
a genuine desire to understand,
if there's a willingness

00:41:31.530 --> 00:41:33.300
to grow, if there's
a willingness

00:41:33.300 --> 00:41:35.340
to not get defensive
if you make a mistake

00:41:35.340 --> 00:41:40.740
and I politely correct you, then
I'll sit it, and I will engage.

00:41:40.740 --> 00:41:44.670
If there's no
willingness, then they

00:41:44.670 --> 00:41:46.985
can come back to
me when they maybe

00:41:46.985 --> 00:41:49.110
grow the heart that they're
lacking in that moment.

00:41:51.870 --> 00:41:54.570
And I think for the
most part, most people

00:41:54.570 --> 00:41:58.860
are in that former category.

00:41:58.860 --> 00:42:02.700
I think most people are
compassionate people.

00:42:02.700 --> 00:42:04.440
Most people are
empathetic people

00:42:04.440 --> 00:42:08.220
that when confronted with a
human being in front of them,

00:42:08.220 --> 00:42:13.636
when confronted with a story,
their hearts will be opened.

00:42:13.636 --> 00:42:15.510
Their minds will be
changed, and their hearts

00:42:15.510 --> 00:42:17.051
will be opened at
least a little bit.

00:42:20.430 --> 00:42:23.250
And so I think
that, well, I don't

00:42:23.250 --> 00:42:27.700
need to spend my time with
someone who's doing this just

00:42:27.700 --> 00:42:30.930
to troll or just to hurt, that
the vast majority of people

00:42:30.930 --> 00:42:32.670
I can engage with
because they are coming

00:42:32.670 --> 00:42:36.630
to me with a genuine willingness
to have their empathy tapped.

00:42:36.630 --> 00:42:39.930
And I think that at the end
of the day, if we do that,

00:42:39.930 --> 00:42:41.550
if we allow
ourselves to do that,

00:42:41.550 --> 00:42:44.640
and if we allow people to make
mistakes, but offer people

00:42:44.640 --> 00:42:47.250
the willingness to grow and
the opportunity to grow,

00:42:47.250 --> 00:42:49.429
that that will make progress.

